
/*
 * This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append the results of [get-nodes] operations to a node. It retrieves nodes specified by [limit] and [offset] from the [.arguments] node and appends them to the current node's children. The [add] slot is used to dynamically extend the node structure based on the retrieved nodes.
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the current node's children.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes specified by the expression from the [.arguments] node for [limit].
 * 3. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes specified by the expression from the [.arguments] node for [offset].
 */
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
